PS.  What is &quot;BAF?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphenom009.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phenom009</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/01 7:43:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Distracted by distraction...</span><hr size=1> You have to target the ground. Push F5(default settings) and you should get a little arrow thingie underneath you. Move the arrow around as if you were moving your character(your character won't move while holding F5). To set where you want simply push F5 again. Then push your designated disctraction key and the mob should turn towards the anwser.<br>
<br>
I am not sure what BAF stand for exactly, I just know that it means MOB's will help each other out. <p>Phenom<BR>
